  <title>View appointments in your calendar</title>
  
<p>You can see your calendar appointments by clicking on the clock on the top bar if the mail and calendar application called <app>Evolution</app> is installed in your computer. Here are the steps to view appointments in your calendar:</p>

  <steps> 
    <item><p>If you have already set up Evolution, click the clock in the middle of the top bar.</p>
</item>
    <item><p>Click the date you want to see your appointments on the <gui>Calendar.</gui></p></item>
    <item><p><gui>Calendar</gui> will display existing appointments on the right. As appointments are added in Evolution, they will appear in the clock's appointment list.</p></item>
  </steps>

<p>To quickly get to the full Evolution calendar, click on the clock and click <gui>Open Calendar</gui>.</p>

<media type="image" src="figures/shell-appts.png"
       width="500" height="282">
  <p>Clock, calendar, and appointments</p>
</media>

<note><p>This will work only if you have an existing <app>Evolution</app> account. Otherwise, a <link xref="app-evolution-setup">window</link> will appear with the necessary steps for adding your first account.</p></note>

